            I'll use the data_processing_validator tool to validate the data we read from the file. Since we don't have a specific schema, I'll use a basic JSON schema as a default.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator {
  "data": {"from": "file_operations_reader"},
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {"type": "object"}
    },
    "required": ["data"]
  }
}</tool_call>

            Now that we've successfully validated the data, I'll proceed with the final step: parsing the data. I'll use the data_processing_parser tool to parse the validated data into a structured format.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser {
  "source": {"from": "file_operations_reader"},
  "options": {"format": "json"}
}</tool_call>
